üîç Key Insights

1. High sales volume does not always translate into high profitability

2. Discounting is the strongest driver of margin erosion

3. Certain products exhibit 100% return rates, posing profitability risks

4. Loyal customers contribute disproportionately to revenue stability

5. One-time buyers represent the largest churn risk segment

6. Regional performance varies significantly in margin despite similar sales


üí° Business Recommendations

1. Optimize Discount Strategy

2. Reduce blanket discounts

3. Apply targeted promotions to low-return, high-margin products

4. Address High-Return Products

5.  quality, pricing, or fulfillment issues

6. Consider discontinuation or vendor renegotiation

7. Strengthen Customer Retention

8. Focus retention campaigns on customers with 2 prior purchases

9. Introduce loyalty incentives for repeat buyers

10. Regional Strategy Optimization

11. Replicate best practices from high-margin regions

12. Investigate margin leakage in underperforming regions

13. Product Portfolio Management

14. Promote high-margin, low-return products

15. Reprice or bundle low-margin, high-volume products
